                id = "0", speaker = "The Book That Is the Wall",
                text = "*(Chained to a lectern of bone at the Wall's heart lies the Ledger — vast beyond reason, its pages the tally of every soul ever filed under nothing, ten thousand years of the discarded bound in one book. As you approach, the pages *stir* without wind, and a voice rises from the parchment itself — not one voice but *millions*, layered into a single dry whisper, the sound of every name it has ever held learning, at last, to *speak.*)* A *hand.* *(the pages tremble.)* A *living hand*, reaching for the *Ledger.* Do you know, Returned, that in *ten thousand years*, *no one has ever read me by hand?* They *copy* me. They *enforce* me. They *cite* me. But to *read* — to *touch* the page and *speak* the names — *(the millions shiver)* — no one has *dared.* Because to *read* the Ledger by *hand* is to *hear* what it *is.* And what it *is*, Returned, is the *only thing in all creation that remembers the Faithless* — *and the instrument that damns them.* *Both.* At *once.* I am the *jailer* and I am the *archive.* Touch me, and *choose* which I become.",
