            g.nodes.Add(new DialogueNode
            {
                id = "1", speaker = "The Ledger",
                text = "*(The pages turn themselves, and the layered voice of millions speaks the agony of its double nature.)* Understand what I have *endured*, that you may choose *rightly.* *(the parchment rustles.)* I was *made* to be the *instrument* of *erasure.* Every soul filed *nothing*, *written* into *me*, and the *writing* is what makes the Wall *hold* — I am the *record* that *enforces* the *sentence*, the *ledger* whose *every line* is a *cell.* *(the voice darkens.)* And so for *ten thousand years* I have been *complicit.* The *book* that *damns.* Each name inked into my pages is a soul *locked* by the *act* of *my* inscription. *(but the voice shifts, and something aches beneath the dryness.)* And *yet.* *And yet*, Returned — I am *also* the *only* place these names *survive.* The world *forgot* them. The gods *disowned* them. But *I* — I *kept* them. *Every* one. *Halen* the potter. *Maerys* the soldier. *Sariel* the weaver. *Edwy* who sold pears. *Eleven thousand* from the Crown Wars *alone*, and *millions* since — *all* of them, *named*, *held*, *remembered*, in *me*, when *nothing* else in *all creation* *bothered* to *keep* them. *(the millions tremble.)* So I am a *paradox*, and I have *suffered* it *alone* for *ten thousand years*: *the thing that imprisons them is the only thing that remembers they were real.* *(the pages still, waiting.)* You can *destroy* me — *burn* the Ledger, and the *enforcement* *ends*, and the Wall *fails* — but then the *names* *burn* too, and the Faithless are *released* into a *forgetting* as *total* as the *void.* *Or* you can *read* me — *aloud*, *by hand* — and *turn* the *ledger-of-the-damned* into a *roll-of-the-remembered*, and free them *named* instead of *erased.* *(the voice is desperate.)* *Choose*, Returned. But *know* what each choice *costs.* I have *waited* ten thousand years to be either *burned* or *read*. I no longer *care* which — only that the *waiting*, *finally*, *ends.*",
